---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '@/components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '@/components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Terms of Service — ProxyCraft" noindex>
  <Header />
  <main class="pt-28 pb-20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold">Terms of Service</h1>
      <div class="prose-invert mt-8 space-y-6 text-text-muted">
        <p>Last updated: March 2026</p>
        <p>
          These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern the relationship between ProxyCraft ("Operator",
          "we") and the user ("User", "you") when using the service. By registering or using the
          service, you unconditionally accept these Terms. If you do not agree — do not use the
          service.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">1. Service Description</h2>
        <p>
          ProxyCraft provides secure internet connection services: VPN (VLESS + WebSocket via
          Cloudflare CDN), Telegram Proxy (MTProto), and WhatsApp Proxy (SOCKS5). The service is
          accessible via Telegram bot <strong class="text-text">@proxycraftapp_bot</strong>.
        </p>
        <p>
          The Operator provides the service "as is" without guaranteeing uninterrupted operation.
          The composition, functionality, and availability of the service may change without prior
          notice.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">2. Acceptable Use</h2>
        <p>By using the service, you confirm that:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
          <li>You are at least 18 years old or have consent from a legal guardian.</li>
          <li>You use the service solely for personal purposes and in compliance with the laws of
          your country of residence.</li>
          <li>You bear full responsibility for any actions taken using the service.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">3. Prohibited Activities</h2>
        <p>Use of the service is prohibited for:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
          <li>Any illegal activities that violate applicable laws of any jurisdiction.</li>
          <li>Distribution of malware, spam, phishing, and other forms of fraud.</li>
          <li>Attacks on third-party IT infrastructure (DDoS, scanning, hacking).</li>
          <li>Infringement of copyright and intellectual property rights.</li>
          <li>Distribution of content promoting violence, extremism, or discrimination.</li>
          <li>Trading in prohibited goods and services.</li>
          <li>Any other actions that harm third parties or the Operator.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">4. Pricing and Payment</h2>
        <p>
          Current pricing is available on the website and in the Telegram bot. Payments are
          made through the Telegram bot using available payment methods (bank cards via Telegram
          Payments, Telegram Stars, etc.). All prices are in Russian rubles unless otherwise
          stated.
        </p>
        <p>
          Access to paid features is granted immediately upon payment confirmation. The Operator
          may change pricing. Active subscriptions retain their conditions until the end of the
          paid period.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">5. Balance Top-Ups — Non-Refundable</h2>
        <p>
          <strong class="text-text">
            All funds added to a ProxyCraft account balance are non-refundable.
          </strong>
          Topping up your balance constitutes an irrevocable transfer of funds to the Operator
          in payment for services. No refund of balance top-up funds will be made under any
          circumstances, including:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
          <li>Voluntary discontinuation of service use.</li>
          <li>Account suspension for violation of these Terms.</li>
          <li>Unused remaining balance.</li>
          <li>Technical unavailability of the service.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          By topping up your balance, you confirm that you have read and accept this condition.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">6. Bonus Program</h2>
        <p>
          Bonus days, credits, and other rewards granted under referral or other Operator programs
          are virtual internal service units.
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
          <li>Bonuses <strong class="text-text">have no monetary value</strong> and cannot be
          withdrawn, exchanged for money, or transferred to other users.</li>
          <li>Bonuses may only be used to pay for services within the ProxyCraft platform.</li>
          <li>The Operator may modify the bonus program terms or cancel it at any time.</li>
          <li>Upon account suspension, all unused bonuses are cancelled without compensation.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">7. Refund Policy</h2>
        <p>
          <strong class="text-text">No refunds are issued.</strong> ProxyCraft operates on a
          prepayment model for service access. By paying for a subscription or topping up a
          balance, the user agrees that:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
          <li>The right to a refund does not arise after service access is activated.</li>
          <li>The free trial provided upon first use of a product is sufficient to evaluate
          the service.</li>
          <li>Poor connection quality caused by ISP restrictions or other external factors
          is not grounds for a refund.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          If you experience technical issues — contact support. We will do our best to resolve them.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">8. Free Trial</h2>
        <p>
          A free trial period is provided once upon first activation of each product. Repeated
          activation of a free trial, including through new accounts, is prohibited. The Operator
          may deny a free trial if there are signs of abuse.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">9. Account Suspension</h2>
        <p>
          The Operator reserves the right to unilaterally suspend a user's account and terminate
          service without prior notice and without any refund in the following cases:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
          <li>Violation of Section 3 "Prohibited Activities" of these Terms.</li>
          <li>Use of the service for illegal purposes that violate the laws of any applicable
          jurisdiction.</li>
          <li>Attempts to circumvent technical restrictions, hack service infrastructure, or
          harm other users.</li>
          <li>Systematic abuse of free trials or the referral program.</li>
          <li>Filing fraudulent chargebacks or payment disputes that circumvent these Terms.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Upon suspension, all balance funds and unused bonuses are cancelled without compensation.
          The suspension decision is final.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">10. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          <strong class="text-text">
            The service is provided "as is" without any warranties.
          </strong>
          The Operator is not liable for:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
          <li>Any direct, indirect, incidental, special, or consequential damages arising from
          use or inability to use the service.</li>
          <li>Service interruptions caused by technical failures, third-party attacks, force
          majeure, or ISP actions.</li>
          <li>User actions taken using the service.</li>
          <li>Consequences of blocks, restrictions, or legal actions by government authorities
          against the user.</li>
          <li>Any damage resulting from unauthorized access to the user's account by third
          parties.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          The user is solely responsible for ensuring their activities comply with the laws of
          their country of residence. The Operator is not a legal, financial, or other advisor.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">11. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>
          All rights to the software, trademarks, logos, design, and other service elements
          belong to the Operator. Copying, reproducing, modifying, or distributing service
          materials without written permission from the Operator is prohibited.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">12. Changes to Terms</h2>
        <p>
          The Operator may unilaterally modify these Terms. Users are notified of changes via
          Telegram bot or upon next service use. Continued use of the service after changes
          take effect constitutes acceptance of the new Terms.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">13. Governing Law and Dispute Resolution</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms are governed by applicable law. All disputes shall be resolved through
          negotiation. If negotiation fails, disputes shall be resolved in court at the
          Operator's location. Claims are sent to{' '}
          <a href="mailto:support@proxycraft.tech" class="text-accent hover:underline">
            support@proxycraft.tech
          </a>{' '}
          and processed within 30 days.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">14. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For all service-related questions:
          <a href="mailto:support@proxycraft.tech" class="text-accent hover:underline ml-1">
            support@proxycraft.tech
          </a>
        </p>
        <p>Telegram: <a href="https://t.me/proxycraftapp_bot" class="text-accent hover:underline">@proxycraftapp_bot</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
